				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What happens with all the KIL opcodes is that a flag responsible for ending the instruction never gets reset, or as <a href="http://visual6502.org/wiki/index.php?title=6502_Unsupported_Opcodes" class="postlink">visual6502</a> puts it &quot;KIL will put the T-state counter into an unrecoverable state&quot;. I like to think of them being infinite sized instructions.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

